"'''Because of You'''" is a song performed by American singer-songwriter [[Kelly Clarkson]]. It was written by Clarkson, David Hodges and Ben Moody while the production was handled by Hodges and Moody. The song was released on August 16, 2005, as the fourth single (third in Europe) from Clarkson's second studio album, ''[[Breakaway (Kelly Clarkson song)|Breakaway]]''. Clarkson originally wrote the first version of "Because of You" when she was 16 years old in order to cope with her parents' divorce. She wanted to include the song on her first album, ''[[Thankful (Kelly Clarkson album)|Thankful]]'', but her request was not accepted by her label. She had to polish the song with Hodges and Moody before successfully convincing her label to include it in ''Breakaway''. 

Lyrically, "Because of You" explores emotional pain from a damaging relationship and critics deemed it is a fiery ode to Clarkson's father. The song begins with a piano-led melody and as it launches into the chorus, a roaring guitar is evident. Critically, "Because of You" garnered positive reviews by most music critics who generally praised Clarkson's vocals. The song performed well commercially; in the United States, it peaked at number seven on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and sold over 1.5 million digital downloads. It was certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA). Internationally, "Because of You" was also a commercial success, topping the charts in the Netherlands and Switzerland and reaching the top five in Australia, Canada, Ireland and United Kingdom. 

The song's accompanying music video was directed by [[Vadim Perelman]]. Clarkson wrote the treatment for the video herself in order to reflect the pain that the she felt due to her parents' divorce. The video's plot centers on Clarkson engaging in a heated argument with her husband in front of her child before realizing that she was repeating her parents' mistake. It won in the category for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Female Video|Best Female Video]] at the 2006 MTV Video Music Awards. The song was performed live at numerous venues, including the [[My December Tour]] (2007) as well as the [[All I Ever Wanted Tour]] (2009). It was covered by several artists including [[Ronan Parke]], who is a runner-up in the [[Britain's Got Talent (series 5)|fifth series]] of ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]''.

==Background and writing==
{{Quote box|width=25%|align=left|quote="My biggest song worldwide is Because of You, and <U+2026> you may as well grab a knife. That song really is the most depressing one I've ever written. I tried to get it on ''Thankful'', and was laughed at and told I wasn't a good writer. So then I tried to get it on ''Breakaway'' <U+2013> and the label saw the results, people responding to it, and allowed it to become a single. Then took credit for its success, of course.|source=<U+2014>Clarkson on trying to get the track into her album, ''Thankful''.<ref name="guardian">{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2011/oct/20/kelly-clarkson-stronger-american-idol|title=Kelly Clarkson: 'I just did it to pay the bills' |date=October 20, 2011|accessdate=January 1, 2012|last=Macpherson|first=Alex|work=[[The Guardian]]|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]. Guardian News and Media}}</ref>}}
[[File:Evanescence 2003 barcelona ben moody.jpg|right|thumb|160px|[[Ben Moody]] was impressed with the song after listening the tape that Clarkson sent him.]]
"Because of You" was written by Clarkson, David Hodges and Ben Moody while the production was handled by Hodges and Moody.<ref name="MTV">{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1506898/kelly-clarkson-chooses-next-single.jhtml|title=Kelly Clarkson Chooses Track Written With Ben Moody As Next Single |date=August 3, 2005|accessdate=January 7, 2012|last=Moss|first=Carey|publisher=[[MTV News]]. [[Viacom]]}}</ref> They also wrote and produced another track entitled "Addicted" that appeared in Clarkson's album ''[[Breakaway (Kelly Clarkson album)|Breakaway]]'' (2004).<ref name="MTV News">{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/bands/c/clarkson_kelly/news_feature/041122/|title=Kelly Clarkson: Just Listen |date=November 22, 2004|accessdate=January 7, 2012|last=Moss|first=Corey|publisher=[[MTV]]. Viacom}}</ref> Clarkson originally wrote the first version of "Because of You" when she was 16 years old as a means of coping with the emotional distress caused by the divorce of her parents.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://top40.about.com/od/kellyclarkson/tp/kclarksonbest5.htm|title=Top 10 Kelly Clarkson Songs|accessdate=January 7, 2012 |last=Lamb|first=Bill|publisher=[[About.com]]. [[The New York Times Company]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/kelly_clarkson/biography/0,,20005758_10,00.html|title=Kelly Clarkson - Biography|accessdate=January 7, 2012|last2=Wong|first1=Janet|last2=Mock|first2=Janet|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time Inc]]}}</ref> She wrote the lyrics of the song in less than 25 minutes.<ref name="MTV News">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cbbc/articles/music-kelly-clarkson-interview|title=Kelly Clarkson Answers Your Questions |date=November 8, 2004|accessdate=January 7, 2012|publisher=[[BBC Online]]. BBC}}</ref>

In an interview with ''[[The Guardian]]'', Clarkson said that she wanted to include the song in her first album, ''[[Thankful (Kelly Clarkson album)|Thankful]]'' (2003), but she was laughed at.<ref name="guardian"/> Then, she took the initiative to polish the song by sending a tape to Moody and worked with Hodges as her songwriting partner. Clarkson explained, "Hearing the Evanescence album, you can obviously tell that David and Ben have a real passion for music and that big kind of background. And I have a big voice and I like the music to match it, so it was a real dream team."<ref name="MTV News"/>

According to Moody, he was very impressed with Clarkson and the song itself, saying "She had these ideas already in place for songs; all I really had to do was build music around them and develop them. It was quite easy."<ref name="MTV"/> Clarkson also admitted that "Because of You" is the most depressing song she has ever written.<ref name="guardian"/> Despite the revelation, she told ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' in August 2011 that she wanted to be remembered for the song because she had to work hard to get it on ''Breakaway'' (2004) when everyone was against it. She added, "I think I<U+2019>m most proud of that song <U+2014> just getting it on an album because no one liked it until it hit no. 1 worldwide and everybody was on board."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2011/08/31/kelly-clarkson-on-the-soundtrack-of-her-life-read-her-exclusive-ew-interview-here/|title=Kelly Clarkson on the soundtrack of her life: Read her exclusive EW interview here|date=August 31, 2011|accessdate=January 6, 2012|last=Goldblatt|first=Henry|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=Time Inc}}</ref>

==Composition==
{{listen
 |filename=Kelly Clarkson - Because Of You.ogg
 |title="Because of You" (2004)
 |description= "Because of You" is a piano ballad composed in E minor.
}}
"Because of You" is a piano ballad<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/column-chartbeat/is-adele-s-someone-like-you-the-first-no-1005349692.story#|title=Is Adele's 'Someone Like You' The First No. 1 Piano-And-Vocal-Only Ballad? |date=September 13, 2005|accessdate=January 16, 2012|last=Trust|first=Gary|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> with a length of three minutes and thirty-nine seconds.<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r718753|pure_url=yes}}|title=allmusic {{{Breakaway > Overview}}}first=Stephen|last=Thomas Erlewine|authorlink=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|accessdate=January 5, 2012|publisher=[[Allmusic]]. [[Rovi Corporation]]}}</ref> According to the sheet music published at Musicnotes.com by [[Alfred Publishing]], it is set in [[time signature|common time]] and has a moderate [[tempo]] of 69 beats per minute. It is composed in the key of [[E minor]] with Clarkson's vocal range spanning over two octaves from G<sub>#3</sub> to E<sub>#5</sub>.<ref>{{cite web|title=Digital sheet music - Kelly Clarkson - Because of You|accessdate=January 5, 2012|work=''Musicnotes.com''|publisher=[[Alfred Publishing]]}}</ref> Bill Lamb of [[About.com]] described the song as "a big pop ballad that expresses raw emotion."<ref name="About.com">{{cite news|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/becauseofyou.htm|title=Because Of You - Kelly Clarkson (RCA)|date=|accessdate=January 5, 2012|last=Lamb |first=Bill |publisher=About.com. The New York Times Company}}</ref> Tony Heywood of [[MusicOMH]] noted that the song's piano arrangement is reminiscent of [[Tori Amos]].<ref name="musicomh">{{cite news|url=http://www.musicomh.com/singles/kelly-clarkson_1105.htm|title=Kelly Clarkson - Because Of You (BMG) |date=November 28, 2005|accessdate=January 5, 2012|last=Heywood|first=Tony|publisher=[[MusicOMH]]}}</ref> Lyrically, "Because of You" is a fiery ode to Clarkson's father,<ref name="Sput">{{cite news|url=http://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/5195/Kelly-Clarkson-Breakaway/|title=Kelly Clarkson Breakaway|date=February 9, 2006|accessdate=January 4, 2012|last=Donnelly|first=Dave|publisher=[[Sputnikmusic]]}}</ref> which is a dark exploration of emotional pain from a damaging relationship.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://top40.about.com/b/2005/08/05/kelly-clarkson-announces-because-of-you-to-be-next-single.htm|title=Kelly Clarkson Announces "Because Of You" To Be Next Single|date=August 5, 2005|accessdate=January 1, 2012|last=Lamb|first=Bill|publisher=About.com. The New York Times Company}}</ref> The song begins with Clarkson singing "oohs" over a somber piano which creates a "wintry tone."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://blogcritics.org/music/article/single-review-kelly-clarksons-because-of/|title=Single Review: Kelly Clarkson's 'Because of You' - Page 2|date=August 19, 2005|accessdate=January 16, 2012| page=2|last=Avoledo |first=Pam|publisher=[[Blogcritics]]. Technorati, Inc}}</ref> As the song launches into the chorus, the roaring guitar is evident,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/breakaway-20041215|title=Kelly Clarkson - Breakaway |date=December 15, 2004|accessdate=January 1, 2012|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]]}}</ref> and the lyrics, "Because of you I never stray too far from the sidewalk / Because of you I learned to play on the safe side so I don<U+2019>t get hurt," were deemed as "touching" by Dave Donelly of [[Sputnikmusic]].<ref name="Sput"/>

==Critical reception==
Film Laureate of Blogcritics considered "Because of You" and "Where is Your Heart" as his two favourite songs from ''Breakaway,'' writing "[Clarkson] commands these two songs like a seasoned pro and directs herself in her songs the way Steven Spielberg said Barbra Streisand directs herself in her songs as if she's directing an actor in a movie."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogcritics.org/music/article/review-kelly-clarkson-breakaway/|title=Review: Kelly Clarkson - Breakaway |date=July 13, 2005|accessdate=January 4, 2012| last=Laureate|first=Film|publisher=Blogcritics. Technorati, Inc}}</ref> Dave Donnelly of [[Sputnikmusic]] compared the song to [[Evanescence]]'s "[[My Immortal]]" (2003). He added that Clarkson managed to take the piano-driven song in a different direction with a "stormy, hard blues vocal... avoiding the typical raised-key final chorus clich<U+00E9> along the way".<ref name="Sput"/> On the other hand, Bill Lamb of About.com lambasted the lyrics of the song and considered it as a 16-year-old work rather than an accomplished pop songwriter.<ref name="About.com"/> Christa L. Titus of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' lauded the song for its absence of schmaltz factor, "only a potent, pained, grown-up anthem of gross betrayal and loss." She concluded her review, writing "it is time for Clarkson to return to No. 1 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]; she has certainly become the most consistent hope for top 40 staple status."<ref>{{cite magazine |last= Titus|first=Christa |date=August 27, 2005|title= Review Spotlights - Singles|magazine= Billboard |volume= 117|issue= No. 35|pages=80 |id= |url= |accessdate=January 7, 2012|publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref> Critics also lauded Clarkson's vocal prowess in the song. Pam Avoledo of Blogcritics thought that vocally, the song is Clarkson's "shining" moment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://blogcritics.org/music/article/single-review-kelly-clarksons-because-of/page-2/|title=Single Review: Kelly Clarkson's 'Because of You' - Page 2|date=August 19, 2005|accessdate=January 5, 2012| page=2|last=Avoledo |first=Pam|publisher=[[Blogcritics]]. Technorati, Inc}}</ref> Tony Heywood of MusicOMH noted that in the song, Clarkson's voice is "full of vulnerability, ache and wounded pride."<ref name="musicomh" /> In May 15, 2007, the song was listed as one of the recipients of BMI Pop Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/534983|title=2007 BMI Pop Awards: Song List |date=May 15, 2007|accessdate=January 11, 2012|publisher=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.|Broadcast Music, Inc]]}}</ref> At the 24th ASCAP Pop Music Awards, the song was honoured with the Most Performed Songs award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/popawards/2007/performed.html |title=ASCAP 2007 Pop Music Awards: Winners List |publisher=[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers]] |accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> On July 2008, [[BBC News]] reported that according to [[PRS for Music|Performing Right Society]], "Because of You" was the second most played song in the United Kingdom over the last five years, following [[Daniel Powter]]'s "[[Bad Day (Daniel Powter song)|Bad Day]] (2005)."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/7508196.stm|title=Powter song is 'UK's most played'  |date=July 16, 2008|accessdate=January 11, 2012| last=|first=|publisher=[[BBC News]]. [[BBC]]}}</ref>

==Chart performance==
"Because of You" entered the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number 99 on the week ending September 3, 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/hot-100?chartDate=2005-09-03&order=gainer|title=Hot 100: Week Ending September 3, 2005|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=January 7, 2012}}</ref> On November 19, 2005, the song peaked at number seven and became her sixth single to reach the top-ten.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/kelly-clarkson/chart-history/498064#|title=Kelly Clarkson Album & Song Chart History|accessdate=January 7, 2012|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100#/charts/hot-100?chartDate=2005-11-19|title=Hot 100: Week of November 19, 2005|accessdate=January 7, 2012|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref> It also topped the [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Pop Songs]] chart on the week ending October 29, 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/song/kelly-clarkson/because-of-you/5651252#/song/kelly-clarkson/because-of-you/5651252|title=Because of You - Kelly Clarkson|accessdate=January 7, 2012|work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref> It became the seventh best selling single of the 2000s decade on the Pop Songs chart complied by ''Billboard''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts-decade-end/pop-songs?year=2009#/charts-decade-end/pop-songs?year=2009|title=Best of the 2000s - Pop Songs|accessdate=January 9, 2012|work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref> On January 31, 2008, "Because of You" was certified [[RIAA certifications|platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA).<ref name="platinum riaa">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?resultpage=1&table=SEARCH_RESULTS&title=Toxic&artist=Britney&startMonth=1&endMonth=1&startYear=1958&endYear=2008&sort=Artist&perPage=25|title=RIAA <U+2014>  Gold & Platinum <U+2013> January 31, 2008|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|accessdate=January 7, 2012}}</ref> As of April 2010, the song has sold 1,537,000 digital copies in the United States, according to [[Nielsen SoundScan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-extra-american-idols-million-sellers.html|title=Chart Watch Extra: American Idol<U+2019>s Million-Sellers |date=April 30, 2010|accessdate=January 7, 2012|last=Grein|first=Paul|publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]]. [[Yahoo!]]}}</ref> In Canada, "Because of You" debuted at number 60 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] on the week ending July 14, 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/canada_singles_top_100/2007/28|title=Canadian Singles Top 100|date=July 14, 2007|accessdate=January 7, 2012|work=Billboard|publisher=acharts.us}}</ref> Two weeks later, the song jumped to a new peak at number 36 and stayed in the position for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/canada_singles_top_100/2007/30|title=Canadian Singles Top 100|date=July 28, 2007|accessdate=January 1, 2012|work=Billboard|publisher=acharts.us}}</ref> It was certified gold by [[Music Canada]] on December 4, 2007 for shipments over 40,000 units.<ref name=mc>{{cite web|url=http://musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?sa=Kelly+Clarkson |title=Gold and Platinum Search (Kelly Clarkson) |publisher=[[Music Canada]] |accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> The single also appeared and peaked on the [[UK Singles Chart]] at number seven on the week ending December 4, 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/uk_singles_top_75/2005/49|title=UK Singles Top 75|date=December 4, 2005|accessdate=January 7, 2012|publisher=acharts.us}}</ref>

In Australia, the song debuted and peaked at number four on the issue dated December 5, 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/australia_singles_top_50/2005/49|title=Australian Singles Top 100|date=December 5, 2005|accessdate=January 1, 2012|publisher=acharts.us}}</ref> It was certified [[list of music recording certifications|gold]] by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA) for shipments over 35,000 units.<ref name="gold aria">{{cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/pages/aria-charts-accreditations-singles-2005.htm|title=ARIA Charts&nbsp;<U+2014> Accreditations <U+2013> 2005 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|accessdate=January 7, 2012}}</ref> The song became the 58th best-selling single in Australia in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/pages/ARIACharts-EndofYearCharts-Top100Singles2006.htm|title=ARIA Charts&nbsp;<U+2014> End of Year Charts <U+2013> Top 100 Singles 2006|publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association|accessdate=January 7, 2012}}</ref> In New Zealand, "Because of You" debuted on [[New Zealand Singles Chart]] at number 37 on the week ending December 5, 2005,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/nz_singles_top_40/2005/49|title=New Zealand Top 40|date=December 5, 2005|accessdate=January 7, 2012|publisher=acharts.us}}</ref> and peaked at number 19 two weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/nz_singles_top_40/2005/51|title=New Zealand Top 40|date=December 19, 2005|accessdate=January 7, 2012|publisher=acharts.us}}</ref> On the week ending March 20, 2006, "Because of You" debuted at number eight on the [[Media Control Charts|German Singles Chart]].<ref name="German">{{cite web|url=http://musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/title/Clarkson%2CKelly/Because+Of+You/single|title=Kelly Clarkson - Because of You (single)|accessdate=January 7, 2012|work=''[[Media Control Charts]]''|publisher=PhonoNet GmbH}}</ref> Three weeks later, it peaked at number four and stayed in the position for three consecutive weeks.<ref name="German"/> The song was certified gold by [[Bundesverband Musikindustrie|The Federal Association of Music Industry]] for shipments over 150,000 copies.<ref name="gold german">{{cite web|url=http://www.musikindustrie.de/gold_platin_datenbank/?action=suche&strTitel=Because+of+You&strInterpret=&strTtArt=alle&strAwards=checked|title=Kelly Clarkson - Because of You |accessdate=January 7, 2012|work=''[[Bundesverband Musikindustrie]]''|publisher=PhonoNet GmbH}}</ref> In Europe, "Because of You" received a commercial success. The song topped the charts in the Netherlands and Switzerland and reached the top five in Austria, Belgium (Flanders), Ireland and Norway.<ref name=acharts>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/song/901|title=Kelly Clarkson - Because of You|year=2005|accessdate=January 8, 2012|publisher=acharts.us}}</ref>

==Music video==
===Development===
The accompanying [[music video]] for "Because of You" was directed by [[Vadim Perelman]] and was produced by Rhonda Vernet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.videostatic.com/vs/tate_usa/|title=New Release: Kelly Clarkson "Because Of You"|first=Steven|last=Gottlieb|publisher=Video Static|date=October 27, 2005|accessdate=January 8, 2012}}</ref> Clarkson wrote the treatment for the video herself in order to reflect the pain that the she felt due to her parents' divorce.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news-article/clarksons-family-oks-painful-break-up-video|title=Kelly Clarkson - Clarkson's Family Ok's Painful Break-Up Video |date=October 5, 2005|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first=|publisher=[[Contactmusic.com]]}}</ref> Nevertheless, Clarkson also allowed Perelman to take control of the production of the video.<ref name="video">{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1510748/kelly-clarkson-fights-with-husband-clip.jhtml|title=Kelly Clarkson Fights With Husband, Sings To Herself In 'Because' Clip |date=September 30, 2005|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=Moss|first=Corey|publisher=[[MTV News]]. Viacom}}</ref> According to Perelman, he wanted to create a disconnection to show "that this kind of dysfunctional family can exist anywhere."<ref name="premiere">{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/music/video/premiere/kelly_clarkson/|title=Kelly Clarkson Video Premiere|date=October 3, 2005|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first=|publisher=MTV. Viacom}}</ref> In an interview with MTV News, Clarkson confessed that the video is sad, rationalizing, "It's a sad song, so the video obviously has to follow that. But it ends really happy and everything and the family, my family, ends up breaking the cycle of my parents."<ref name="video"/> Since the music video deals specifically with her parents' divorce, Clarkson had to seek for her parent's permission. She explained,
<blockquote>
"It's very close to home [for me]. I OK'd it with my family and everything because they think it's important, because we're obviously very different now than we were when we were younger. And it's important for people to see that raw kind of emotion that happens in life. It sucks sometimes, so it's important to see that I think. And that's what we're portraying in the video."<ref name="video"/>
</blockquote>
In the video, the younger version of Clarkson is played by Kennedy N<U+00F6>el, the daughter of her musical director, Jason Halbert.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.j-14.com/2011/12/j-14-video-majors-minors-kennedy-noel-this-holiday-music-video.html|title=J-14 Video: Majors & Minors' Kennedy N<U+00F6>el's "This Holiday"|date=December 2, 2012|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first=|publisher=[[J-14 (magazine)|J-14]]. Bauer Publishing}}</ref> The music video of "Because of You" premiered on October 3, 2005, on ''[[Total Request Live]]''.<ref name="premiere"/>

===Synopsis===
[[File:kellyclarksonbecauseofyouvideo.png|thumb|right|230px|Clarkson and younger Clarkson (played by Kennedy N<U+00F6>el) in the music video of "Because of You."]]
The video starts at the Clarkson's household. There, she and her partner are engaged in a heated argument, and at one point he threatens to smash a picture of the family. Time freezes still and her husband becomes immobile; Clarkson, however, is immune to this. Looking around her house, she sees her younger self. Hand in hand, the younger and older versions of Clarkson relive her troubled childhood as various painful memories are seen, such as the younger Clarkson making a picture for her father, who tosses it into the sink, and Clarkson's mother making an unappreciated dinner for her father. These events drive her mother to the point of taking pills and crying in front of the younger Clarkson. The breaking point is finally seen when Clarkson's parents have a physical fight and throw objects at each other. Soon after, Clarkson's father packs his bags and leaves; although the younger Clarkson tries to get him to stay, he pulls away. The older Clarkson runs back in time to the present. There, time unfreezes and instead of fighting with her husband, they make up. They then see that their daughter in the video had seen them fight, and they embrace her and each other. Throughout the music video, Clarkson is shown singing on the front porch, her mother's bed and a room full of mirrors, reflecting an image of her younger self.<ref name="video"/>

===Reception and accolades===
Elizabeth Black of [[VH1]] ranked the music video at number four in her list of "Five Emotive Music Video Performances." She reasoned, "Kelly Clarkson practically sobs her way through this hurt and angry expression of the pain that the narrator<U+2019>s father has caused her through his absence and lack of love."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://blog.vh1.com/2011-07-22/tearin-up-my-heart-the-top-five-emotive-music-video-performances/|title=Tearin<U+2019> Up My Heart: The Top Five Emotive Music Video Performances |date=July 22, 2011|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=Black|first=Elizabeth|publisher=[[VH1]]. Viacom}}</ref> The music video won the category of [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Female Video|Best Female Video]] at the [[2006 MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/ontv/vma/2006/|title=2006 Video Music Awards |date=August 31, 2006|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first= |publisher=MTV. Viacom}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://top40.about.com/od/awards/a/mtvvma2006wu.htm|title=2006 MTV Video Music Awards The Wrapup|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=Lamb|first=Bill |publisher=About.com. The New York Times Company}}</ref> This marks the second time Clarkson has won the same category two years in a row; her first win in the category was at the [[2005 MTV Video Music Awards]] for the music video of "[[Since U Been Gone]]."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://goldderby.latimes.com/awards_goldderby/kelly_clarkson/|title=Which 'American Idol' rivals have the best shot to win awards?|date=March 19, 2009|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=Derby|first=Gold |publisher=''[[Los Angeles Times]]''. [[Tribune Company]]}}</ref> The music video was also nominated for the category of [[MTV Video Music Award - Viewer's Choice|Viewer's Choice Award]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/shakira-red-hot-chili-peppers-dominate-2006-vma-nominee-list-20060731|title=Shakira, Red Hot Chili Peppers Dominate 2006 VMA Nominee List|date=July 31, 2006|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first= |publisher=''Rolling Stone''. Wenner Media}}</ref> but lost to [[Fall Out Boy]]'s "[[Dance, Dance]]" (2005).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/in_pictures/5304698.stm|title=In pictures: MTV Music Video Awards |date=September 1, 2006|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first= |publisher=[[BBC News Online]]. BBC}}</ref> At the [[2006 MuchMusic Video Awards]], the music video won the category of [[2006 MuchMusic Video Awards#People.27s Choice: Favourite International Artist|People's Choice: Favourite International Artist]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.muchmusic.com/events/mmva06/winners/|title=Winners - PC: Favourite International Artist|date=June 18, 2006|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first=|publisher=[[MuchMusic]]. Bell Media}}</ref> The video was also nominated at the [[MTV Australia Video Music Awards 2006|2006 MTV Australia Video Music Awards]] in the category of [[MTV Australia Video Music Awards 2006#Best Pop Video|Best Pop Video]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://top40-charts.com/news.php?nid=22298|title=MTV Australia Video Music Awards - Vote Now! The Darkness & The Veronicas Set To Perform, Madonna Tops Nominations, The Veronicas, Bernard Fanning, Green Day, Foo Fighters, Wolfmother & Kanye West Follow With Three Noms Each |date=March 4, 2006|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first= |publisher=Top40-Charts.com}}</ref> but lost to [[Ashlee Simpson]]'s "[[Boyfriend (Ashlee Simpson song)|Boyfriend]]" (2005).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.tv/news/VMA-s-hit-Oz-13138/|title=The MTV Australia Video Music Awards honouring the best in music video, rolled into Sydney at the Sydney Super Dome on Wednesday (April 12th)|date=April 14, 2006|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=|first= |publisher=MTV. Viacom}}</ref> According to Jocelyn Vena of MTV, the video for "Because of You" was referenced in [[Taylor Swift]]'s music video for "[[Mine (song)|Mine]]" (2010), writing "When Swift's character remembers the fights her parents used to have, her memories mirror Clarkson's attempts to exorcise the demons of her past to find love in her future."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1646711/taylor-swifts-mine-recalls-popculture-love-stories.jhtml|title=Taylor Swift's 'Mine' Recalls Pop-Culture Love Stories|date=August 27, 2010|accessdate=January 8, 2012|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|publisher=MTV. Viacom}}</ref>

==Live performances==
Clarkson performed "Because of You" at the [[48th Grammy Awards]] which took place on February 8, 2006, at the [[Staples Center]] in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. Donning a red dress and singing from beside a grand piano, her performance in that event garnered positive reviews from critics. Elysa Gardner of ''[[USA Today]]'' lauded Clarkson's performance and ranked it as one of the three best performances, writing, "The pre-performance clip of a girlish-looking Clarkson emphasized how little Kelly has matured. The girl most likely to escape the ''[[American Idol]]'' stigma was in fine, creamy voice, and kept the Mariah-esque riffing to a minimum."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/music/awards/grammys/2006-02-09-three-best_x.htm|title=Three best, and the rest|date=February 9, 2006|accessdate=January 9, 2012|last=Gardner|first=Elysa|publisher=''[[USA Today]]''. [[Gannett Company]]}}</ref> Robert Lloyd of ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' considered Clarkson's performance as one of the highlights in the event and described her performance as a "thin-skinned rendition [...] in which her whole being seemed involved."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2006/feb/09/entertainment/et-review9|title=Doing what they do the best: music|date=February 9, 2006|accessdate=January 9, 2012|last=Lloyd|first=Robert|publisher=''Los Angeles Times''. Tribune Company}}</ref> [[Yahoo! Music]] praised Clarkson's rendition of the song, calling it "perfectly fine" despite the saying that it was "a little reminiscent of those many mediocre, superficial ballads trotted out on 'Idol.'"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://music.yahoo.com/kelly-clarkson/news/clarkson-surprises-with-grammy-performance--29504357|title=Clarkson Surprises With Grammy Performance|date=February 8, 2006|accessdate=January 9, 2012|last=|first=|publisher=Yahoo! Music. Yahoo!}}</ref> On August 21, 2007, Clarkson performed "Because of You" and "[[Never Again (Kelly Clarkson song)|Never Again]]" (2007) on the [[Canadian Idol (season 5)|fifth season]] of ''[[Canadian Idol]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.straight.com/article-106663/kelly-clarkson-on-canadian-idol|title=Kelly Clarkson on Canadian Idol|date=August 22, 2007|accessdate=January 9, 2012|last=Lucas|first=John|publisher=''The Georgia Straight''. Vancouver Free Press Publishing Corp.}}</ref>

"Because of You" was performed at the [[My December Tour]] (2007). Clarkson's performance of the song was accompanied only by [[Wurlitzer|Wurlitzer organ]] that earned her a prolonged ovation when she sent her voice soaring into the rafters.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://blogs.courant.com/eric_danton_sound_check/2007/10/review-kelly-clarkson-at-moheg.html | title=Review: Kelly Clarkson at Mohegan Sun | author=Danton, Eric R. | publisher=''[[Hartford Courant]]'' | publisher=Tribune Company |date=August 22, 2007 | accessdate=January 12, 2012}}</ref> While touring at [[Beacon Theatre (New York City)|Beacon Theatre]], [[New York City]], Clarkson performed the song using only one keyboard, which was deemed by Donna Freydkin of ''USA Today'' as the most memorable moment of the event.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/music/news/2007-10-14-clarkson-tour_N.htm|title=Kelly Clarkson opens tour in an intimate setting|date=October 15, 2007|accessdate=January 12, 2012|last=Freydkin|first=Donna|publisher=''USA Today''. Gannett Company.}}</ref> She also performed the song using only a keyboard as an instrument during her tour at [[Massey Hall]], [[Toronto]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.soulshine.ca/reviews/liveReview.php?lrid=267| title=Kelly Clarkson<U+2019>s <U+2018>My December<U+2019> Comes To Life at Massey Hall | author=Matt Borrelli | publisher=[[Soul Shine Magazine]] | date=October 30, 2007| accessdate=January 12, 2012}}</ref> "Because of You" was also performed at the [[List of Kelly Clarkson concert tours#All I Ever Wanted Tour|All I Ever Wanted Tour]] (2009). Clarkson's performance of the song during the tour in the [[Hammerstein Ballroom]], New York City, was given a positive review by Jim Cantiello of MTV. He explained that Clarkson's powerful rendition "literally stopped the show [...] for almost 30 seconds because the audience erupted in such wild applause."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1623261/kelly-clarkson-concert-giant-karaoke-party.jhtml|title=Kelly Clarkson Fans Turn New York Concert Into A Giant Karaoke Party|date=October 8, 2009|accessdate=January 9, 2012|last=Cantiello|first=Jim|publisher=MTV. Viacom}}</ref> Caryn Ganz of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' noted that Clarkson sang the song to pay homage to [[Reba McEntire]] who was in the audience.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/kelly-clarkson-mixes-biggest-hits-with-white-stripes-kings-of-leon-covers-in-new-york-20091007|title=Kelly Clarkson Mixes Biggest Hits With White Stripes, Kings of Leon Covers in New York|date=October 7, 2009|accessdate=January 12, 2012|last=Ganz|first=Caryn|work=Rolling Stone. Jann Wenner LLC}}</ref>

