==Cover versions==
On June 4, 2011, ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]'' contestant, [[Ronan Parke]] covered "Because of You" in the finale of the [[Britain's Got Talent (series 5)|fifth series]] of the show. His performance garnered standing ovation from the audience as well as the four judges.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1394321/Britains-Got-Talent-2011-Winner-Jai-McDowall-beats-bookies-favourite-Ronan-Parke.html|title='Dark horse' Jai McDowall beats bookies favourite Ronan Parke to win Britain's Got Talent|date=May 6, 2011|first=Emily|last=Sheridan|work=[[Daily Mail]]|publisher=[[Associated Newspapers Ltd]]|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> Parke also recorded the song and included it in his debut album, ''[[Ronan Parke (album)|Ronan Parke]]''. In an interview with [[Digital Spy]], Parke stated that it was really challenging to record "Because of You." He added, "I asked the producer if we could leave out some of the big notes. We left them until the end and I was actually a bit scared by the noise that came out of me - I didn't know I could sound that loud!"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/interviews/a346596/ronan-parke-interview-this-year-feels-unreal.html|title=Ronan Parke interview: 'This year feels unreal'|date=October 20, 2011|first=Robert|last=Copsey|accessdate=January 11, 2012|publisher=Digital Spy. Hachette Filipacchi M<U+00E9>dias}}</ref> [[Lisa Tucker (singer)|Lisa Tucker]] covered the song on the [[American Idol (season 5)|fifth season]] of ''[[American Idol]]''. However, her performance was met with negative reviews from the judges and she was consequently eliminated from the show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1527429/mighty-tuck-tucker-satisfied-with-results.jhtml|title=Lisa 'Mighty Tuck' Tucker Says She's Satisfied With Results|date=June 30, 2006|first=Corey|last=Moss|work=''MTV''|publisher=Viacom|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1527406/idol-voters-end-lisa-tuckers-run.jhtml|title=Lisa Tucker's 'American Idol' Run Ends|date=June 30, 2006|first=|last=|work=''MTV''|publisher=Viacom|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> "Because of You" was also covered by Kim Bo Kyung, who was a contestant in South Korean singing competition show, ''[[Superstar K2]].'' Her performance received positive response from the judges and was considered as one of the highlights in the show even though she failed to advance into the Top 11.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2010/11/superstar-ks-kim-bo-kyung-to-release-single-because-of-you|title=Superstar K<U+2019>s Kim Bo Kyung to release single "Because of You"|date=November 12, 2010|first=Jeshicaa|last=|work=Allkpop|publisher=6Theory Media|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> Following her elimination, she recorded the studio version of "Because of You" which was released as a digital download by [[Sony Music Entertainment]] due to an overwhelming demand.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2010/12/superstar-k2s-kim-bo-kyung-signs-with-sony-music|title=Superstar K2<U+2032>s Kim Bo Kyung signs with Sony Music|date=December 22, 2010|first=Kimchisteve|last=|work=Allkpop|publisher=6Theory Media|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> She also received a personal video message from Clarkson who gave her words of advice and support.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/09/kim-bo-kyung-receives-a-video-message-from-her-idol-kelly-clarkson|title=Kim Bo Kyung receives a video message from her idol, Kelly Clarkson|date=September 27, 2011|first=Vitalsign|last=|work=Allkpop|publisher=6Theory Media|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> The song also was covered by [[Orange Caramel]], a South Korean [[girl group]], on Christmas Day for [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s special programme, "ICON".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2010/12/orange-caramel-performs-kelly-clarksons-because-of-you-on-icon|title=Orange Caramel performs Kelly Clarkson<U+2019>s "Because of You" on MBC<U+2019>s "ICON"|date=December 25, 2010|first=Casper|last=|work=[[Allkpop]]|publisher=6Theory Media|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref>

===Reba McEntire and Kelly Clarkson version===
{{Infobox single <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Songs -->
