In 2007, Clarkson recorded "Because of You" as a duet with American country singer [[Reba McEntire]]. The song was released as a single on May 15, 2007, as the lead single for McEntire's album, ''[[Reba: Duets]]''. The duet garnered mixed reviews from critics who felt that even though McEntire's singing was pleasant, she brought nothing new to the song. At the [[50th Grammy Awards]], McEntire and Clarkson received a nomination in the category of Best Vocal Country Collaboration for the song. In the United States, "Because of You" became McEntire's seventh song to peak at number two at [[Hot Country Songs]]. It also became Clarkson's first song to appear on the chart. The music video was directed by [[Roman White]] which depicts McEntire and Clarkson as two retro Hollywood lounge singers. The plot centers on Clarkson's relationship with her abusive partner which is witnessed by McEntire. The song was performed live by the two singers in various venues, notably at the [[Academy of Country Music#2007|42nd Annual Academy of Country Music Awards]] and during their [[2 Worlds 2 Voices Tour]].

====Background and composition====
{{Listen|pos=left|filename=Reba McEntire & Kelly Clarkson - Because Of You.ogg|title="Because of You" (2007)|description=A 21 second sample of "Because of You", which incorporates the sound of guitar, strings, cymbals and violin.}}
According to McEntire, Clarkson was the first singer to pair up with her for the album ''[[Reba: Duets]]'' (2007).<ref name="pair">{{cite news|url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/music/news/2007-09-18-reba-main_N.htm|title=Kelly Clarkson finds her idol in Reba McEntire|date=September 19, 2007|accessdate=January 9, 2012|last=Mansfield |first=Brian|publisher=''USA Today''. Gannett Company}}</ref> She also claimed that "Because of You" was not the original song to be included in the album; it was another song that she recorded with Clarkson entitled "A Lot Like You"<ref name="Scripps Networks Interactive">{{Cite news|url=http://www.gactv.com/gac/home/article/0,,GAC_26057_5634431,00.html|title=Reba's Heartfelt Duet with Kelly Clarkson|date=July 18, 2007|first=|last=|work=[[Great American Country]]|publisher=[[Scripps Networks Interactive]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> McEntire explained that it was Narvel, her husband, who convinced her to go back in the studio and record "Because of You" after he heard both McEntire and Clarkson rehearsing the song.<ref name="pair"/> She expressed, "Narvel saw it. That wasn't one of the songs we had talked about recording <U+2014> matter of fact, Kelly and I had already recorded a song, 'A Lot Like You,' for the duet project, and he said, 'You've got to do this one together,' so we did."<ref name="Scripps Networks Interactive"/> Musically, the song is different from the original version. Thom Jhurek of [[Allmusic]] described the duet version as "a big, overblown power ballad" which incorporates "guitars compressed to the breaking point, sweeping strings, and enormous crashing cymbals."<ref name="thom">{{Cite news|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/reba-duets-r1205391/review|title=Reba Duets|first=Thom|last=Jhurek|accessdate=January 10, 2012|publisher=Allmusic. Rovi Corporation}}</ref> The use of violin was also incorporated into the duet, giving it a melodramatic quality that was deemed "unnecessary" by Nancy Dunham of Blogcritics.<ref name="blogcritics">{{Cite news|url=http://blogcritics.org/music/article/music-review-reba-mcentire-reba-duets/|title=Music Review: Reba McEntire - Reba Duets|date=October 15, 2007|first=Nancy|last=Dunham|accessdate=January 10, 2012|publisher=Blogcritics. publisher=Technorati, Inc}}</ref> The song was officially sent to radio stations on May 15, 2007, as the lead single from the album.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/mcentire-surrounded-by-stars-on-reba-duets-1003583688.story#|title=McEntire Surrounded By Stars On 'Reba Duets'|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> It was added to country radio playlists on May 28, 2007.<ref name="us_radio">[http://gfa.radioandrecords.com/publishGFA/GFANextPage.asp?sDate=05/28/2007&Format=4 Country <U+2013> Week Of: May 28, 2007 ] [[Radio & Records]]. May 28, 2007. Retrieved January 9, 2012</ref>

====Critical reception====
The song received mixed reviews from critics. Lana Cooper of [[PopMatters]] loved the duet and deemed it as "the most unique track on the album."<ref name="popmattersduo" /> She also felt that McEntire and Clarkson complemented each other in the song, writing "The double-feature cover of Clarkson<U+2019>s hit showcases two women with exceptional and distinctive voices playing to one another<U+2019>s strengths."<ref name="popmattersduo">{{Cite news|url=http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/reba-mcentire-reba-duets|title=Reba McEntire: Reba Duets|date=October 22, 2007|first=Lana|last=Cooper|accessdate=January 10, 2012|work=PopMatters. }}</ref> The same opinion was echoed by Nancy Dunham of Blogcritics who believed that "the two use just the right amount of vocal passion to make the ardent lyrics come alive, but stay out of the cheese zone."<ref name="blogcritics"/> Scott Sexton of [[About.com]] lauded the duet version of the song, writing "As of now anything Reba touches turns to gold, but with this hit alone she has a great shot at platinum."<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://countrymusic.about.com/od/cdreviewsmz/fr/Reba_Duets.htm|title=Reba McEntire - Duets|first=Scott|last=Sexton|work=''About.com''|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|accessdate=January 10, 20122}}</ref> Kevin John Coyne of Country Universe praised McEntire's beautiful singing although he said that she did not bring "anything new" to the song.<ref name="countryuniverse">{{Cite news|url=http://www.countryuniverse.net/2007/10/06/album-review-reba-mcentire-reba-duets/|title=Reba McEntire, Reba Duets|date=October 6, 2007|first=Kevin|last=Coyne| first2=John|last2=|work=''Country Universe''|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> He also added that the song "had the potential to be reworked into an interesting mother/daughter confrontation" but he was disappointed because McEntire did not change the viewpoints of the song.<ref name="countryuniverse" /> He graded the production of the song as "C-", writing "The end result is the song doesn<U+2019>t make any sense, and is just confusing to listen to."<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.countryuniverse.net/2007/05/19/review-reba-mcentire-featuring-kelly-clarkson-because-of-you/|title=Reba McEntire featuring Kelly Clarkson, "Because of You"|date=May 19, 2007|first=Kevin|last=Coyne| first2=John|last2=|work=''Country Universe''|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> Thom Jurek of Allmusic criticized the instrumentation of the song, saying "This could have been a [[Meat Loaf]] reject from [[Bat Out of Hell II: Back Into Hell|Bat out of Hell II]]."<ref name="thom"/> Gayle Thompson of The Boot ranked "Because of You" at number ten in his list of "Top 20 Reba McEntire songs".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theboot.com/2011/03/28/top-reba-mcentire-songs/|title=Top 20 Reba McEntire Songs|date=March 28, 2011|first=Thompson|last=Gayle|work=The Boot|publisher=[[AOL]]|accessdate=January 10, 20122}}</ref> He also included both McEntire and Clarkson at number six for their duet of "Because of You" in his list of "Cross Country: Top 10 Country-Pop Duets."<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theboot.com/2011/09/14/country-duets-songs/|title=Cross Country: Top 10 Country-Pop Duets|first=Thompson|last=Gayle|work=The Boot|publisher=AOL|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> Gary Trust of ''Billboard'' listed the pair as one of the 10 all-female hit collaborations that have scaled ''Billboard'' charts in recent years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/10-all-female-hit-collaborations-1005154152.story#|title=10 All-Female Hit Collaborations|date=April 26, 2011|first=Gary|last=Trust|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref>

At the [[Academy of Country Music#2007|42nd Annual Academy of Country Music Awards]], McEntire and Clarkson received a nomination in the category of Musical Event of the Year for "Because of You," but lost to [[Tracy Lawrence]] with [[Kenny Chesney]] and [[Tim McGraw]] for their collaboration in "[[Find Out Who Your Friends Are]] (2006)."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://countrymusic.about.com/od/2007cmaawards/a/CMAWinners07.htm|title=Winners at the 2007 Country Music Association Awards|accessdate=January 11, 2012 |last=Fabian|first=Shelly|work=''About.com''|publisher=The New York Times Company}}</ref> At the [[50th Grammy Awards]], McEntire and Clarkson received a nomination in the category of Best Vocal Country Collaboration for the song, but lost to [[Willie Nelson]] and [[Ray Price (musician)|Ray Price]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/grammys-kanye-winehouse-springsteen-clean-up-early-20080210|title=Grammys: Kanye, Winehouse, Springsteen Clean Up Early|date=February 10, 2008|accessdate=January 11, 2012 |last=|first=|work=Rolling Stone|publisher=Wenner Media}}</ref> The pair also received a nomination for the Vocal Event of the Year at the [[Academy of Country Music#2008|2008 Academy of Country Music]], but lost to Tracy Lawrence with Kenny Chesney and Tim McGraw for their collaboration in "Find Out Who Your Friends Are."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://countrymusic.about.com/od/2008acmawards/a/ACMWinners08.htm|title=ACM Winners - Find out who won at the 2008 ACM Awards.|accessdate=January 11, 2012 |last=Fabian|first=Shelly|work=''About.com''|publisher=The New York Times Company}}</ref> At the 2008 ASCAP Country Music Awards, the song was honoured with the Most Performed Songs award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/ascapcma/2008/winners.aspx|title=Complete List of Winners |publisher=American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers |accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref>

====Chart performance====
[[File:Reba McEntire & Kelly Clarkson - Encore.jpg|thumb|right|upright|McEntire and Clarkson singing "Because of You" as part of the encore in [[2 Worlds 2 Voices Tour]].|alt=Image of two blond women walking down a step of stairs on the stage. An image of guitarist is seen standing next to them. Behind them, a set of drum and a cello are seen.]]
In the United States, "Because of You" debuted at number 42 on the [[Hot Country Songs]] on the week ending June 2, 2007.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/country-songs#/charts/country-songs?chartDate=2007-06-02&order=gainer|title= Country Songs Week of June 02, 2007 |date=June 2, 2007|first=|last=|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/chart-beat-1003590119.story#/|title=Chart Beat|first=|last=|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://countrymusic.about.com/od/hotcountrysongsof2007/a/052807_hotcntry.htm|title=Top 10 Hot Country Songs for Week of May 28, 2007|date=May 28, 2007|first=Shelly|last=Fabian|publisher=[[About.com]]|accessdate=January 9, 2012}}</ref> On the week ending September 8, 2007, the song jumped to its new peak at number two and was held off the top spot by [[Rodney Atkins]]' "[[These Are My People]] (2007)."<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/country-songs?chartDate=2007-09-08#/charts/country-songs?chartDate=2007-09-08|title= Country Songs Week of September 08, 2007 |date=September 8, 2007|first=|last=|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> It became McEntire's seventh song to peak at number two, and her first in over ten years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/features/chart-beat-1003636166.story#/features/chart-beat-1003636166.story|title= Chart Beat
|first=|last=|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref>
Had the song jumped to number one, it would have been McEntire's 23rd number one song on the chart as well as the first remake of a pop song to top Hot Country Songs since [[Mark Chesnutt]]'s cover of [[Aerosmith]]'s "[[I Don't Want to Miss a Thing]]" spent two weeks at number one in 1999.<ref>{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com.my/books?id=EikEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA109&lpg=PA109#v=onepage&q&f=false|title= Chart Beat|date=September 15, 2007|accessdate=January 10, 2012| last=Bronson|first=Fred|work=Billboard}}</ref> "Because of You" also made an appearance on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number 52,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.music.yahoo.ca/read/news/45019827|title= Rihanna, Shop Boyz Still Not Budging On Hot 100 |date=July 5, 2007|first=Jonathan|last=Cohen|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> and peaked at number 50.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-extra-it-takes-two.html|title= Chart Watch Extra: It Takes Two |date=September 29, 2011|first=Paul|last=Grein|work=Yahoo! Music|publisher=Yahoo!|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> In Canada, the song peaked at number 36 on the week ending July 21, 2007.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/artist/Reba+McEntire/chart-history/2434?f=793&g=Singles|title= Reba McEntire Chart History |date=July 21, 2007|first=|last=|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref>

====Music video====
The music video, directed by [[Roman White]], debuted on June 21, 2007.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cmt.com/videos/reba-mcentire/157908/because-of-you-featuring-kelly-clarkson.jhtml|title= Videos : Reba McEntire : Because of You (featuring Kelly Clarkson) |accessdate=January 11, 2012|publisher=Country Music Television. Viacom}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/reba-mcentire-kelly-clarkson/313901/because-of-you.jhtml|title=Reba McEntire & Kelly Clarkson - Because of You |date=June 22, 2007|first=|last=|work=''MTV''|publisher=Viacom|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref> It depicts McEntire and Clarkson as 1930's Hollywood lounge singers. In the video, McEntire encounters Clarkson attempting to conceal a bruise inflicted by the latter's abusive partner. When Clarkson's boyfriend is fighting with her, McEntire leaves the dressing room. While performing on stage, Clarkson witnesses her boyfriend flirting with another woman. After the performance, she smashes a vase out of anger in the dressing room. Her boyfriend enters the room to take her out for the rest of the evening. Though apprehensive, Clarkson leaves on his arm before looking back uncertainly at McEntire, who uncomfortably fiddles with a hairbrush as she watches them leave. The music video hit number one on CMT's [[Top 20 Countdown]] on September 13, 2007.
<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cmt.com/shows/dyn/top_twenty_countdown/series_wildcard.jhtml?wildcard=/dynamic_templates/shows/center_templates/wildcard/top_twenty_countdown/2007/countdown_091307_main.jhtml&event_id=885814|title=Top 20 From Week of September 13, 2007 |date=September 13, 2007|accessdate=January 11, 2012|last=Moss|first=Carey|publisher=Country Music Television. Viacom}}</ref> At the [[CMT Music Awards#2008|2008 Country Music Television Awards]], the music video received nominations for three awards. It received a nomination for the Video of the Year, but was lost to [[Taylor Swift]]'s "[[Our Song (song)|Our Song]]" (2007) and for the Collaborative Video of the Year, but lost to [[Bon Jovi]] featuring [[LeAnn Rimes]], "[[Till We Ain't Strangers Anymore]]" (2007). Roman White, who directed the music video, received a nomination for the Video Director of the Year, but lost to [[Michael Salomon]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://theenvelope.latimes.com/awards/env-cmt-2008-awards10apr10-list,0,2748012.htmlstory|title= 2008 CMT Music Awards scorecard |date=April 10, 2008|first=|last=|work=Los Angeles Times|publisher=Tribune Company|accessdate=January 11, 2012}}</ref>

====Live performances====
McEntire and Clarkson first performed "Because of You" together at the 42nd Annual Academy of Country Music Awards in May 2007.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/08290/920090-42.stm|title=How Kelly met Reba|date=October 16, 2008|first=Scott|last=Mervis|work=[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]|publisher=John Robinson Block|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> A month later, the pair performed the song in an episode of [[CMT Crossroads]] at [[Ryman Auditorium]] which debuted on [[Country Music Television]] on June 24, 2007.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cmt.com/news/country-music/1562982/kelly-clarkson-reba-mcentire-feel-the-love-at-cmt-crossroads.jhtml|title=Kelly Clarkson, Reba McEntire Feel the Love at CMT Crossroads|date=June 20, 2007|accessdate=January 10, 2012|publisher=Country Music Television. Viacom}}</ref> On September 19, 2007, they appeared on ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]]'' where they sang the song together.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.oprah.com/oprahshow/Superstar-Duets/9|title=Superstar Duets|date=September 19, 2007|accessdate=January 10, 2012|publisher=[[Oprah.com]]. [[Harpo Productions|Harpo Productions, Inc.]]}}</ref> "Because of You" was also performed as the encore of the [[2 Worlds 2 Voices Tour]] (2008), a co-headlining concert tour by McEntire and Clarkson.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://readingeagle.com/article.aspx?id=110313|title=CONCERT REVIEW: Country meets pop as Reba McEntire and Kelly Clarkson strut their stuff|date=August 20, 2008|first=Susan|last=C. Stein|work=[[Reading Eagle]]|publisher=William S. Flippin|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref>

